"My Way" is a profound reflection on the human journey, particularly the masculine one, which carries a silent and often unspoken hardness. The line "What has he got, if not himself" is not just a celebration of self-reliance but an acceptance of the solitude that often comes with the courage to live on one's own terms. Over time, you realize this song isnt about glory or perfectionits about resilience and authenticity, even in the face of regrets and tough choices. A masterpiece that only deepens with maturity.
